      "replies_count": 2,
      "reblogs_count": 0,
      "favourites_count": 8,
      "quotes_count": 0,
      "edited_at": null,
      "content": "<p>First of all, the concept is so useful, we want it on the host too, i.e. have additional breakpoints *after* the initrd\u2192host transition, and that means Dracut is no longer in control then.</p><p>Secondly, there&#39;s a push towards avoiding initrd generators altogether and instead building initrds just like any other OS disk image (see for example mkosi-initrd), directly from distro packages, using the same codepaths as are used after the initrd\u2192host transition.</p>",
      "reblog": null,
