      "edited_at": null,
      "content": "<p><span class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"><a href=\"https://the.gayest.dev/@Sparky\" class=\"u-url mention\">@<span>Sparky</span></a></span> you certainly can. But only really in very simple setups. Thing is anything non-trivial really should do disk encryption for the rootfs and that implies some userspace. Either to do the tpm stuff, or to query user for pw, or to do fido2. Its not going to happen that the kernel will do all that itself</p><p>But sure if you have a very simple device, dont care about authentication/encryption of the basic OS file systems and have no complex storage, sure you can do without initrd, already today.</p>",
